article.headline: Lafayette 80, Navy 67
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Freshman guard Andrew Brown scored 17 points and Jamaal Hilliard added 13 to lead Lafayette to an 80-67 win over Navy on Saturday. Greg Sprink led the way with 17 points for Navy (6-9, 0-3 Patriot League) which jumped out to a 31-20 lead with 6:53 to go in the first half. After that, Lafayette (8-7, 2-1) went on a 43-8 run that lasted into the middle of the second half. Paul Cummins added 13 points and Bilal Abdullah had 10 as the Leopards had four players scoring in double figures. Lafayette built up a 46-39 lead less than four minutes into the second half, and jumped out to its largest lead of the game, 64-39, with 10:18 to go. Navy trimmed the lead to 73-60 with 3:38 to go, but Lafayette converted 8-of-10 shots from the foul line in the final 3:50 to hold off the rally. Sprink led four players scoring in double figures for Navy. Corey Johnson and David Hooper each had 11, while Kaleo Kina added 10.
